{
  "stem": "9878.2",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] Now, we'll continue a little bit later.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't know if it was in-- if it was in July or it was in August.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Naturally, I didn't look at the time on the calendar.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I know and I walked the street, and I saw a German with a long leather coat, even though it was July.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was a warm day.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he had a Hakenkreuz-- it means  a swastika-- on his arm ban, with a high hat.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And written down on the hat-- because I had good eyesight then, and I took a look.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I see-- when I saw him, I saw that it  was written on, [? 'Der Tod.' ?] And he had with them a dog, a German dog, like a-- like a-- like a wolf, a big dog.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I saw an old Jewish man walking across the street, near-- not on the sidewalk, but near the sidewalk, on the-- where the [INAUDIBLE] were running, because a Jew is not supposed to walk on the sidewalk.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Walking on the sidewalk is the penalty of death.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Getting water by the river is penalty of death.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I'll explain to you what water of the river what has happened.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "First, I'll start with [INAUDIBLE] this SS man.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I don't know his name.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "He is anonymous.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "But I saw his actions.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "All of us saw and heard the German holler to the dog-- Jude! 'Jude' in German means Jew.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he pointed to this man walking across the street on the side-- near the sidewalk.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And the dog ran after him, turned around, jumped up his hind legs on-- across his throat-- dropped him.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "All I hear is the man screamed, oy!",
      "word_count": 8
    }
  ],
